# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Vercel environment variables — split into client and server scope
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT: keys WITHOUT the VITE_ prefix stay server-only (Vercel
# Functions in /api/*). Keys WITH the VITE_ prefix are baked into the
# client bundle and visible to anyone who opens DevTools.
#
# AI provider keys (Groq + Gemini) MUST stay non-VITE_ — they're sensitive.
# Supabase URL + anon key are PUBLIC by design and need VITE_ to reach the
# browser client. The anon key only allows operations within RLS policies.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI providers (server-only — used by /api/*)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Groq — primary optimizer. Free tier: 1,000 RPD on llama-3.3-70b-versatile.
# Get a key (free) at: https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# Gemini — fallback optimizer + all toolkit generators (cover letter, etc.)
# Free tier: 20 RPD on gemini-2.5-flash. Get a key at:
# https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase (public — both client and server use these)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
